Preheat oven to 350 degrees F. Combine ketchup, brown sugar and mustard in small bowl; set aside. Combine 1/3 cup ketchup mixture and remaining ingredients in large bowl; mix well. Shape mixture into loaf in large shallow baking dish. Bake 1 hour and remove from oven. Pour remaining ketchup mixture over loaf and bake an additional 10 minutes. Let stand 5 minutes before slicing. Serve hot. Refrigerate leftovers.